Quote:  [The Wanganui river] has also a good many islands in it, upon which the beautiful yellow kowai grass grows in abundance, giving the river a very pretty appearance. [ed fn] Presumably a misprint, for no kowhai <i>grass</i> is known to botanists. The manuscript diary here refers to `groves of kowai' ...
